\subtree[fre-00N4]{
\title{Conservative maps}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Definition}
\date{2026-04-13}

\p{
A map is \em{conservative} if it is right orthogonal to the morphism inclusion into
the [walking isomorphism](Synthetic.Categories.WalkingIso)
#{\Delta^1 \to \mathfrak{I}}.
}

\agda{
module ConsMap = RightOrthogonalClassClosure (point arrow-‚ĄĎ)

is-conservative
  : {ūĚď§ ūĚď• : Level} {A : Type ūĚď§} {B : Type ūĚď•} ‚Üí (A ‚Üí B) ‚Üí Type (ūĚďė ‚äĒ ūĚď§ ‚äĒ ūĚď•)
is-conservative = ConsMap.‚ąąR

conservative-map : {ūĚď§ ūĚď• : Level} ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď• ‚Üí Type (ūĚďė ‚äĒ ūĚď§ ‚äĒ ūĚď•)
conservative-map A B = ő£[ f ‚ą∂ (A ‚Üí B)] is-conservative f

open ConsMap public using () renaming
  ( ‚ąąR‚Üźbase-change to is-conservative‚Üźbase-change
  ; ‚ąąR‚Üźequiv to is-conservative‚Üźequiv
  ; ‚ąąR‚Üźequiv' to is-conservative‚Üźequiv'
  ; ‚ąąR‚Üźis-equiv to is-conservative‚Üźis-equiv
  ; ‚ąąR-iff‚Üźequiv to is-conservative-iff‚Üźequiv
  ; ‚ąąR‚Üźretraction to is-conservative‚Üźretraction
  ; ‚ąąR-‚ąė to is-conservative-‚ąė
  ; ‚ąąR-left-cancel to is-conservative-left-cancel
  ; ‚ąąR‚Üźhomotopy to is-conservative-homotopy
  ; ‚ąąR-‚ąė~ to is-conservative-‚ąė~
  ; ‚ąąR-left-cancel~ to is-conservative-left-cancel~)
}
}

\subtree[fre-6EF2]{
\title{A map is conservative if and only if it reflects isomorphisms}
\taxon{Lemma}

\agda{
module _ {ūĚď§ ūĚď•} {A : Type ūĚď§} {B : Type ūĚď•} where

  reflects-isos : (A ‚Üí B) ‚Üí Type (ūĚďė ‚äĒ ūĚď§ ‚äĒ ūĚď•)
  reflects-isos F = {x y : A} (őĪ : Hom A x y) ‚Üí is-iso (ap-hom F őĪ) ‚Üí is-iso őĪ
}

\p{
This is yet to be formalised.
}
}

